# Cloudflare Pages response headers.
#
# Some locked-down networks (government/corporate proxies such as Navy NMCI)
# ignore revalidation directives and pin a stale copy of a page or asset. That
# is what froze the tools: the proxy kept serving a weeks-old, broken copy of
# the Calculator and Dispersity pages while a cache-busted URL fetched the
# current, working one. `no-store` tells every intermediary not to hold a copy
# at all, so each request reaches the live file.
#
# This does not hurt performance or offline use: the in-browser service worker
# caches assets explicitly (independent of this header) and serves repeat loads
# from its own cache. Keeping sw.js itself un-stored also ensures service-worker
# updates always propagate instead of being pinned by a proxy.
/*
  Cache-Control: no-store
